## The Nature of the Thu'um

The **Thu'um** (pronounced "THU-oom"), also called **the Voice** or **Storm Voice**, is the ability to concentrate one's life force into **Shouts** — words of power in **Dovahzul** (the dragon tongue) that alter reality.

This is not magic in the conventional sense. The Thu'um is an expression of **pure will** channeled through a deep understanding of a concept. Each Shout is composed of three **Words of Power** which, when combined, produce a specific effect.

## Dragons and Language

For **Dragons**, the Thu'um is their very nature — to speak is to act, and every word they utter carries a fraction of power. Dovahzul is not merely a language: it is a direct expression of reality itself.

The most powerful dragons could wield:
- **Unrelenting Force** (Fus Ro Dah) — project a wave of force
- **Fire Breath** (Yol Toor Shul) — breathe devastating flames
- **Frost Breath** (Fo Krah Diin) — freeze everything in their path
- **Dragonrend** (Joor Zah Frul) — force a dragon to comprehend mortality (created by mortals)

## The History of the Voice

### The Dragon Cult (Merethic Era)
The first humans of Skyrim lived under the dominion of dragons. The **Dragon Priests** served as intermediaries and oppressed the people.

### The Rebellion (Late Merethic Era)
The goddess Kynareth (Kyne) took pity on the mortals and sent **Paarthurnax** — a renegade dragon — to teach the Thu'um to humans. The first human **Tongues** used this power to overthrow the draconic yoke.

Three heroes — **Hakon One-Eye**, **Gormlaith Golden-Hilt**, and **Felldir the Old** — used the Shout **Dragonrend** and an Elder Scroll to cast Alduin out of the timestream.

### Jurgen Windcaller (1E 416)
After the Nordic defeat at the **Battle of Red Mountain**, the warrior Jurgen Windcaller spent seven years meditating on the reasons for the failure. He concluded that the Thu'um should be used as a tool of **veneration**, not of war.

He founded the order of the **Greybeards** and the doctrine of the **Way of the Voice** — to use the Thu'um only for contemplation and the honoring of the gods.

### The Dovahkiin (4E 201)
The **Dovahkiin** (Dragonborn) is a mortal born with the soul of a dragon — capable of absorbing the souls of defeated dragons and learning Shouts instantly, whereas a Greybeard spends decades mastering a single Word.

## Notable Shouts

| Shout | Dovahzul | Effect |
|-------|----------|--------|
| Unrelenting Force | Fus Ro Dah | Shockwave that hurls everything away |
| Fire Breath | Yol Toor Shul | Devastating flames |
| Slow Time | Tiid Klo Ul | Dilates the flow of time |
| Call Dragon | Od Ah Viing | Summons an allied dragon |
| Dragonrend | Joor Zah Frul | Forces a dragon to land |
| Storm Call | Strun Bah Qo | Summons a thunderstorm |
